’ 37. Havings land. That is, by marriage. For the Levites had no other lands of their own, except what they had by their wives, as twe have observed upon the preceding verse. A memorable example to others is this alienation of his dowry land by Barnabas, not to supply his own, but the wants of others. For a small farm of this nature used to be very highly valued by the pos- sessors, insomuch that they were unwilling to part with it, and they seem to sell their lives to the purchasei that bought it.
